The paper proposes a deep neural network for automatic detection of cancer metastasis from whole slide images, which involves computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The network architecture is based on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and includes pyramidal feature aggregation, which is a common technique in CV and image processing. The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and computation cost, which is a common concern in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DL (Machine Learning and Deep Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which are all relevant to the paper's topic and methodology.
